main event: Two witnesses reported observing an object, which was concluded to be a probable satellite, moving from southeast to northwest.
interesting points: The object was observed for a total of about 5 minutes., The observed path appeared to be straight but may have varied slightly in direction., The object appeared and disappeared intermittently., It was estimated to be larger than an average star and emitted blue-white light., No physical evidence or photographs were collected.
witness description: two witnesses who observed the object visually
